SIMPLE: silicate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Silicate
<hw>Sil"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>silicate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt of silicic
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In mineralogical chemistry the silicates include; the
<xex>unisilicates</xex> or <xex>orthosilicates</xex>, salts of
orthosilicic acid; the <xex>bisilicates</xex> or
<xex>metasilicates</xex>, salts of metasilicic acid; the
<xex>polysilicates</xex> or <xex>acid silicates</xex>, salts of the
polysilicic acids; the <xex>basic silicates</xex> or
<xex>subsilicates</xex>, in which the equivalent of base is greater than
would be required to neutralize the acid; and the <xex>hydrous
silicates</xex>, including the zeolites and many hydrated decomposition
products.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silicated</ent>⟦br⟧
